<TEXT>
summer replacement series gave television 
viewers some alternatives during the july fourth holiday week but 
reruns got the top ratings 
networks put the dogs on said david marans a senior 
researcher for the j walter thompson advertising agency these 
are shows that will not be on the fall schedule almost without 
exception the public has not liked these shows 
according to ac nielsen co ratings released tuesday the four 
halfhours of nbcs toprated thursday night lineup won the weeks 
highest ratings it was the first time since february that nbc had 
the top four shows 
a cheers rerun was no 1 a repeat of the cosby show was 
second the pilot episode of blossom a potential midseason 
entry was third and a repeat of the seinfeld chronicles pilot 
was fourth 
marans said ratings for blossom were boosted by having 
cosby precede it just as the toprated cheers episode 
pulled up the seinfeld ratings 
those shows were all weaker than the repeats that went on 
before them marans said the networks have got to be very 
disappointed 
blossom turned in the best performance for an nbc pilot so 
far this summer the network said the comedy stars mayim bialyk 
who plays a 13yearold coming of age in los angeles 
the second highestrated summer sitcom was abcs dads a 
dog which stars david steinberg it opened in 21st place 
overall nbc was the no 1 network for the eighth consecutive 
week with a 90 average but was barely ahead of abc which had an 
89 average cbs was third with a 76 average the fox broadcasting 
co had a 60 average 
a rating point represents 921000 households 
nbc has won 39 of the past 42 weeks but marans said nbcs 
losses and abcs gains will have the two networks closely battling 
for first place in the weeks ahead 
rounding out the top 10 shows were cbs designing women and 
60 minutes at fifth and sixth nbcs empty nest at no 7 
nbcs golden girls and cbs murphy brown tied for eighth 
and abcs roseanne and foxs married with children tied 
for 10th 
fox had two other shows in the top 20 in living color at 
no 15 and cops at 17 
in the evening news broadcasts abc continued its domination 
with an 84 rating cbs was second with a 74 rating and nbc was 
third with a 69 
