<TEXT>
former gov arch a moore jr whose 
crimes included extorting more than half a million dollars from a 
coal operator has been sentenced to five years and 10 months in 
prison and fined 170000 
moore 67 appeared stoic during his sentencing tuesday on five 
corruption charges he was ordered to report to a federal prison in 
petersburg va on july 31 
arch moore is a criminal assistant us attorney joe savage 
said before sentencing if there is one thing missing from that 
man its remorse 
moore pleaded guilty to charges of mail fraud extortion 
obstruction of justice and filing false income tax returns during 
his 1984 and 1988 campaigns and during his third term from 198589 
us district judge walter hoffman on monday had refused to let 
moore withdraw his guilty pleas moore had argued he was coerced by 
federal prosecutors 
moore a republican who also was a us congressman for 12 
years refused to comment on the sentence an appeal is pending 
defense attorney william hundley said 
moores corruption involved campaignfunding violations not 
raids on the treasury hundley said 
i submit he served well and honorably hundley added 
us attorney michael carey said moore likely will serve at 
least 2 years before being considered for parole 
moore served as governor from 1969 to 1977 and again from 1985 
to 1989 longer than any governor in the states history he was 
only the second republican since 1933 to govern west virginia 
where democrats outnumber republicans by a 2to1 margin 
moore pleaded guilty may 8 to extorting 573000 from coal 
operator h paul kizer of beckley in return for a 21 million 
refund from the states black lung fund which provides benefits to 
coal miners 
moore also pleaded guilty to trying to block a federal grand 
jury investigation into corruption in his administration and 
allegations he used illegal cash contributions in his 1988 campaign 
he also admitted filing false income tax returns in 1984 and 
1985 and defrauding the state of his salary and benefits by 
funneling 100000 in illegal cash payments into his 1984 campaign 
to buy votes 
hoffman sentenced moore to five years on the extortion charge 
six months on mail fraud and two years each on the tax fraud 
counts all are to be served concurrently moore also got 10 months 
for the obstruction of justice charge which carries a mandatory 
prison term 
moore could have gotten 36 years in prison and fines of 125 
million 
moore is not the first west virginia governor to be convicted on 
federal charfes democrat ww wally barron who served from 
1961 to 1965 was convicted of bribing the foreman of a jury that 
acquitted him of bribery in 1968 he served three years and four 
months of a 12year sentence 
