<TEXT>
forget about the thornier negotiations between 
the economic summit partners jackson hicks master caterer knows 
what real pressure is 
pressure is serving lunch to the most powerful leaders in the 
western world no dropped trays no splashy food no hardtoeat 
entrees nothing that might embarrass a president or hinder a 
negotiation or interrupt a profound thought 
ive enjoyed taking care of many important people in my career 
kings queens presidents movie stars businessmen hicks 
said but nothing was more challenging and exciting than taking 
care of those world leaders 
hicks 43 might be considered the man who catered the summit 
his houston company put on 13 meals and parties from a 
5000person media festival to a working lunch for the leaders 
hes averaged less than two hours of sleep a night through the 
summit which ends today with a party to thank houston hosted by 
president bush and catered by hicks 
were used to pressure but this has been a very intense thing 
because of who these people are and because of the short window of 
time hicks said everythings been on scheduled and come off 
without a hitch except for one flat tire on the way to a 
spouses dinner where barbara bush was host 
it hasnt been easy intense security measures especially when 
moving around the rice university campus has doubled preparation 
times hicks said and tuesday his 170 workers served three 
working luncheons at once 
you have to make the food simple not flashy and not 
difficult to eat you want to be unobtrusive they cant carry on 
an important conversation if theyre trying to crack a lobster 
open he said this isnt the time to bring out some flaming 
desert on the shoulders of a team of waiters 
