the last us ambassador to cambodia 
john gunther dean said today he plans to return to phnom penh to 
help heal the wounds of 20 years of conflict 
dean now retired from government service was ambassador when 
the khmer rouge defeated the usbacked phnom penh government in 
1975 vietnam drop the khmer rouge from power in late 1978 and 
installed a prohanoi regime 
clutching an american flag dean and his staff were evacuated by 
helicopters april 12 1975 as the khmer rouge closed in on the 
capital 
dean who is to fly to phnom penh on thursday and stay about a 
week said he would try to arrange a thai educational exchange and 
look into the possibility of hotel construction by an indian 
company to promote tourism 
what i can do is to help cambodia and the people of cambodia 
find ways to bring them out of isolation and into cooperation with 
the rest of the world dean said in an interview 
i believe that the time of healing of wounds from 20 years of 
conflict should be seized he said 
fighting continues between the government of prime minister hun 
sen and a threemember guerrilla group that includes the khmer 
rouge who are supported by china the two other noncommunist 
groups are backed by the united states 
