the judge overseeing the settlement of the 
governments racketeering lawsuit against the teamsters union has 
ordered broad supervision of the unions upcoming election 
complete supervision of all facets of the election process is 
the only way to guarantee the integrity of the elections and 
encourage extensive rank and file participation us district 
judge david n edelstein said tuesday in approving new election 
rules 
the judge made more stringent the new voting procedures proposed 
by a courtappointed administrator he gave the elections 
administrator michael holland authority over some election 
functions previously assigned to officers of the local unions 
the supervision in this election must indeed be expansive and 
proactive edelstein said 
