pleased with the wests economic health celebrating the 
renaissance of democracy throughout much of the world the 
leaders offered this outlook 
the upbeat language of the final communique masked sharp 
differences on trade and the environment compromises were struck 
on both subjects to allow everyone to claim victory or at least 
harmony 
