the government likely will default on its debt 
for the first time next month unless congress raises the limit 
before leaving aug 6 on its monthlong recess the treasury 
department warned on wednesday 
treasurys current estimates show that the permanent ceiling 
of 312 trillion will be sufficient only until midaugust 
treasury undersecretary robert r glauber told the house ways and 
means committee 
the nations debt topped the 3 trillion mark last april and by 
monday had surpassed 309 trillion 
while glauber did not say how much of an increase was needed 
immediately he did provide estimated ceilings for the next three 
fiscal years to guide congressional and white house budget 
negotiators as they continue their budgetcutting talks 
we estimate that a debt limit of 351 trillion will be 
sufficient to last through the 1991 fiscal year that begins oct 
1 he said current estimates indicate a need for ceilings of 381 
trillion through fiscal 1992 and 405 trillion through fiscal 1993 
rep sam gibbons dfla expressed anger that the bush 
administration was planning to add hundreds of billions of dollars 
to the national debt 
hes the president of the united states hes convinced the 
voters they dont need to pay for anything we can just keep on 
borrowing gibbons said my answer to him is no 
