warning last month that the governments estimates are uncertain 
because of difficulty in predicting the cash needed to bail out the 
savings and loans industry 
the government narrowly averted its first default last november 
when congress raised the debt limit from 28 trillion for the 
fiscal year ending sept 30 it also had come close to default on 
several other occasions 
the national debt has more than tripled since the beginning of 
the decade as the treasury was forced to borrow more and more money 
to finance government spending that exceeds tax receipts 
the annual deficits have gone down from their peak of over 200 
billion a year but the deficit still totaled 1521 billion in the 
year ending last sept 30 it totaled 15168 billion after the 
first eight months of the current fiscal year and some analysts say 
it could return to the 200 billion level again by years end 
