new york university president john brademas 
credited with transforming the university from a commuter school to 
a national university will step down next year officials said 
wednesday 
brademas who came to nyu in 1981 after 11 terms as a democratic 
congressman from indiana will step down as president in december 
1991 said nyu spokesman virgil renzulli 
he would officially retire in march 1992 at age 65 after a 
nearly threemonth sabbatical 
brademas would become president emeritus and help the university 
raise money and develop its international programs 
under his tutelage nyu basically went from a commuter school 
with most of our students coming from the metropolitan new york 
area and became a major national research university renzulli 
said 
during his tenure brademas recruited top faculty members and 
saw enrollment soar to about 40000 students he also helped raise 
800 million and increase the universitys endowment from 2875 
million to 540 million 
to ease his departure the responsibilities of nyu chancellor l 
jay oliva considered a likely successor have been expanded to 
include oversight of campus construction and the implementation of 
new programs 
laurence a tisch chairman of the nyu trustees said the board 
hopes to name a new president before brademas leaves 
the university founded in 1831 employs 12000 people has an 
