designated president of the ebrd to undertake in close 
consultation with the commission of the european communities a 
detailed study of the soviet economy to make recommendations for 
its reform and to establish the criteria under which western 
economic assistance could effectively support these reforms this 
work should be completed by years end and be convened by the imf 
we took note of the importance to the government of japan of the 
peaceful resolution of its dispute with the soviet union over the 
northern territories 
