<TEXT>
east german beer brewers and farmers 
temporarily blocked west german border crossings with their trucks 
wednesday to protest what they said is unfair competition from the 
west 
the government meanwhile threatened to close retail stores to 
stop price gouging by former stateowned businesses now feasting on 
the nations new free market 
the government said it would take tough measures to break up the 
retail monopolies that have been charging arbitrarily high prices 
in the country since it shifted to a market economy on july 1 
east germany merged its economy with west germanys on that date 
and began using the west german mark as its official currency 
former stateowned grocery and gas station chains that once sold 
goods at governmentset levels have raised many prices 
dramatically some of them even higher than in wealthy west germany 
government spokesman matthias gehler said west german food 
retailers agreed to send mobile shops with their goods to 
compete against the east german firms 
the government last week said it would break up the chains by 
selling individual stores 
the cabinet of prime minister lothar de maiziere on wednesday 
issued an order saying that employees of the giant ho grocery and 
retail chain would have the first opportunity to buy those stores 
de maiziere toured two grocery stores in east berlin and 
threatened to close shops and levy fines on stores guilty of price 
gouging 
he also criticized the fact that only 15 percent of the goods 
sold in the stores he visited were produced in east germany the 
rest were western products 
my impression confirms the reports ive read he said we 
will see what we can quickly do about this 
east germanys beer brewers blocked a west german border points 
in the southwest corner of the country for about 30 minutes 
creating huge traffic snarls the east german news agency adn said 
it said the domestic brewers have lost 90 percent of their 
business since east germany opened its doors to western products on 
july 1 
rainer doetsch head of the castle brewery accused west german 
brewers of dumping their beer in east germany at belowmarket 
prices 
meanwhile farmers in the agricultural heartland of the north 
blocked a main highway leading to the west german border with 
scores of tractors and trucks adn said 
farmers say the refusal of east german retailers to stock their 
goods in favor of west german products is denying them a chance to 
compete 
many east german retailers have signed agreements with west 
german grocery chains that prevent them from stocking many east 
german goods in their stores 
