would be used to replant deforested areas relocate settlers and 
patrol the amazon to stop slashandburn devastation of the vast 
jungle 
scientists say slashandburn destruction of amazon rain forest 
by ranchers and farmers releases carbon dioxide in the atmosphere 
and adds to the greenhouse effect which increases the earths 
temperature 
this wouldnt be charity goldemberg told the associated 
press the developed countries would be defending their own 
interests by stopping the global warming 
an average of 8700 square miles of rain forest has been cut and 
burned each year since 1978 or about 8 percent of the 
2millionsquaremile wilderness goldemberg said 
he said the data was obtained from brazils space research 
institute based on 222 landsat satellite photos of the rain forest 
earlier estimates of amazon destruction had ranged from 5 to 20 
percent 
