<TEXT>
american airlines inc is adding 1 to 
4 to the cost of a ticket at five airports to help pay for what it 
calls exorbitant and intolerable fees at airports 
other airlines said they would not follow the lead of the 
nations largest carrier and analysts dont expect the surcharges 
to establish a norm within the industry 
i dont see that as any particular trend said lee howard 
vice president of consulting firm airline economics inc in 
washington it deals with a specific issue which has arisen and 
american airlines has chosen to see that way as covering what they 
consider to be excessive expenses 
al becker spokesman for fort worthbased american said the 
increased charges will amount to about 4 million a year they will 
take effect sunday at new yorks laguardia airport newark 
international airport new orleans international airport palm 
beach international airport in west palm beach fla and southwest 
florida regional in fort myers fla 
the fees range from 4 per ticket in newark to 150 in new 
orleans and 1 for the other three airports analysts doubted the 
increases would affect americans business because they are small 
compared to average ticket prices of 200 
the fees will be applied only to local boardings at those 
airports so they will not affect people passing through or coming 
home the company said 
its very simple and straightforward becker said at 
those five airports we are covering what we believe to be excessive 
and unreasonable costs it only makes good business sense to do 
that 
becker said increases involve budget overages or charges at 
those specific airports that go far beyond what they ought to be 
becker said 
at laguardia for example the complaint involves a floor 
covering used in renovations 
american is not trying to exert control over budgets at local 
airports becker said but we are in the position of explaining 
to the airports what we believe is fair and equitable based on our 
experience 
there is simply no way that we can tolerate those sorts of 
unreasonable charges said becker who noted that two or three 
years ago american implemented a similar surcharge at the las vegas 
airport because the local airport authority wanted to build an 
outlandishly extravagant new terminal 
