<DOCNO> AP900711-0226 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here is a rundown of important events in the birth and evolution 
of apple computer inc 
januarymarch 1976 computer enthusiasts steve wozniak 26 and 
steve jobs 21 assemble a new computer circuit board with no 
keyboard or case they call it apple i 
april 1976 wozniak and jobs form the apple computer co on 
april fools day 
may 1976 jobs sells his volkswagen and wozniak sells his 
hewlettpackard programmable calculator raising 1350 to finance 
production of apple i boards they begin building the boards in 
jobs garage 
july 1976 apple i board released for sale to computer 
enthusiasts for 66666 
november 1976 apple formulates a business plan for sales to 
reach 500 million in 10 years the company will pass the mark in 
half that time 
january 1977 apple is formally incorporated by its founders 
and a group of venture capitalists it moves from jobs garage into 
a building in cupertino calif 
april 1977 apple unveils the apple ii the first personal 
computer that can generate color graphics its widely recognized 
as a quantum leap in the industry 
june 1977 apple ii becomes available to the general public for 
1298 monthly orders reach a 1 million annual sales rate first 
apples are shipped to europe 
january 1978 apple moves into new cupertino headquarters 
which eventually acquires a campuslike quality as other apple 
buildings spring up around it 
december 1978 apple becomes one of the fastestgrowing us 
companies with a 10fold increase in sales and a dealer network 
exceeding 300 
february 1979 apple proclaims its own business goal of no 
more typewriters 
juneseptember 1980 apple opens customer support and 
manufacturing centers in several us locations as well as cork 
ireland and zeist the netherlands the beginnings of a major 
international expansion 
december 1980 apple goes public in one of the biggest stock 
offerings ever undertaken with 46 million shares priced at 22 
each snapped up within minutes apples staff surpasses 1000 and 
its distribution network becomes the largest in the world 
februarymarch 1981 apple streamlines internal operations and 
restructures top management jobs becomes chairman 
august 1981 international business machines corp introduces 
its personal computer partly because of the enormous competitive 
pressure created by apple december 1982 apple becomes the first 
personal computer company to reach a 1 billion annual sales rate 
april 1983 john sculley formerly president of pepsico 
becomes apples president and ceo his ascendance marks the 
beginning of what will become a clash of management styles and 
directions in the company 
may 1983 apple enters the fortune 500 club of biggest us 
industrial corporations at no 411 
january 1984 apple unveils the 2495 macintosh quickly 
recognized as one of the most significant advances in personal 
computing because its so easy to operate 
february 1985 wozniak resigns the first serious public 
indication of a profound management rift 
june 1985 sculley announces a major reorganization that will 
halve manufacturing facilities to three and cut the work force by 
20 percent the first quarterly loss in the companys history is 
reported because of the cost associated with the reorganization 
september 1985 jobs resigns another major creative loss and a 
dramatic display of management feuding he starts a new computer 
venture next inc 
september 1986 apple introduces the 999 apple iigs personal 
computer organizes nationwide to attract new users and opens a 
washington office as part of a strategy to win more government 
contracts 
april 1987 apple declares its first quarterly cash dividend of 
12 cents a share and announces a twoforone stock split 
march 1988 apple sues microsoft corp and hewlettpackard co 
for alleged copyright infringement of the macintosh system 
august 1988 sculley announces another reorganization creating 
four new subdivisions apple usa apple products apple education 
and apple europe 
september 1988 in a major strategy shift apple redesigns 
computers to accommodate ibm software acknowledging the need for 
compatibility with competitive products 
september 1989 apple introduces the portable macintosh a 
17pound 6000 laptop aimed at fighting a wave of new competitors 
january 1990 apple usa president allan z loren once 
considered sculleys likely successor quits after his division 
shows persistent declines in profit and market share the company 
freezes salaries cuts staff and eliminates some benefits 
reflecting a slump 
march 1990 apple products president jeanlouis gassee who 
oversaw newproduct development resigns effective september 
may 1990 apple faces a significant new threat from microsoft 
which devises software to give ibm personal computers the same 
userfriendly graphics of the macintosh 
june 1990 apple announces that robert puette a longtime 
hewlett packard executive will head apple usa filling the vacancy 
created by lorens departure 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

