of conflict of interest in his role as a director of silverado 
which loaned millions of dollars to a bush business partner who 
never repaid the money 
bush said tuesday the investigation by regulators is 
selfserving 
the regulators are politically motivated he told the ap in 
denver 
bush said he had performed properly and that all loans that 
came before the directors were for projects previously approved by 
others more knowledgeable than he 
several former silverado executives have settled charges with 
regulators and have effectively been barred from future positions 
in the thrift and banking industry 
