from august 1985 to august 1988 voted to approve loans or business 
deals totaling more than 45 million to a business partner bill l 
walters 
an administrative law judge is scheduled to hear the bush case 
sept 25 in denver before making a recommendation to ots director 
timothy ryan 
abc said the lawsuit would charge that the negligence of 
silverados directors partly caused the losses the network quoted 
an unnamed source as saying that the negligence was particularly 
egregious 
it said the suit would contend the silverado directors acted 
irresponsibly in approving dozens of questionable loans the 
evidence for the suit abc said includes a memo in which a top 
silverado executive acknowledged that the board was a rubber 
stamp for the thrifts officers when it approved several loans 
bush and other former directors and officers of silverado 
testified in hearings in may and june before the house banking 
committee 
president bush who has pledged to vigorously prosecute fraud in 
the savings and loan industry has said he has full confidence in 
the integrity and honor of his son the president also has 
promised not to interfere with the investigation 
the ots documents alleging conflict of interest by neil bush 
were first disclosed in reports by the denver post the rocky 
mountain news and the washington post 
