differences with senior management 
entertainment weekly has commanded intense interest since its 
launch in february because it is the first weekly from the time 
inc magazine co since the costly failure of its tvcable week 
magazine in 1983 
it also is being watched to see how evenhanded a publication 
can be when it is offering opinions on movies music and the like 
from sister companies and their competitors 
media analysts also wonder how patient debtheavy time warner 
will be for the magazine to become profitable time warner has a 
106 billion debt resulting from time incs purchase last year of 
warner communications inc 
magazine executives refuse to disclose how the magazine is doing 
financially startup costs reportedly were more than 30 million 
publisher michael j klingensmith said it is on target with an 
average 600000 circulation and is ahead of projections in ad 
revenues despite a weak market 
jarvis and klingensmith are credited for separately conceiving 
the concept for the magazine six years ago entertainment weeklys 
mission would be to give busy people a onestop guide on how to 
entertain themselves 
the heart of the magazine has been reviews of entertainment 
products television movies music videos books and magazines 
feature stories focused on how the products were made not gossip 
about the celebrities in them 
after less than three weeks on the new job seymore said in an 
interview that reviews would remain the centerpiece but added the 
magazine has a wider mandate 
he wants more feature and news coverage of entertainment such 
as the magazines recent stories on tvs use of fbi videotapes of 
washington dc mayor marion barrys drug arrest 
seymore wants more information on the opinion pages than readers 
have been getting to help them decide what might be worthwhile to 
watch read or hear 
and he said readers can look for shorter reviews and features 
some staffers feared jarvis departure meant the magazine would 
