said was a response to complaints from readers and advertisers that 
the magazine was cluttered and hard to read 
the cover was simplified the logo straightened and a column 
that ran along the edge of each cover touting other stories was 
dropped the news amp notes columns that ran along the edges of 
each section were given separate pages at the end of each section 
a bolder typeface and heavier paper were used 
the magazine also adopted a new approach to choosing cover 
topics instead of running covers relating to products just being 
released cover stories now will focus on products that have been 
out for awhile 
the old approach left the magazine with some arcane and esoteric 
covers such as one about vietnam novels said the magazine groups 
editorial director richard stolley the new approach will mean 
more mainstream covers which could help sales he said 
jarvis declined comment on his reasons for resigning 
