covered too many subjects and was too intellectual to attract a 
mass audience every week walker also thinks it is too late to save 
it 
but john gray a top media planner at the ad agency j walter 
thompson said he remains bullish on the magazine there is a 
tendency to expect that a new magazine will come out of the womb 
already perfect and grown up and thats unrealistic he said 
