<TEXT>
copper futures prices leaped to their highest levels in two 
months wednesday amid heavy buying by west german interests and 
renewed supply concerns 
on other commodity markets precious metals were mixed grains 
nd soybeans retreated energy futures advanced and livestock and 
meat futures were mixed 
copper futures settled 29 cents to 575 cents higher on new 
yorks commodity exchange with the contract for delivery in july at 
12435 a pound the highest settlement of a nearterm copper 
contract since may 11 
prices shot up from the opening bell in reaction to a sharp 
increase in copper prices on the london metal exchange that 
analysts attributed to strong buying from west germany 
market ruors linked the buying to a west german company said to 
be part of a consortium trying to buy a large stateowned copper 
mine in cananea mexico 
the german firm was believed to have sold forward contracts in 
london earlier because it believed the mexican government would 
accept the groups bid for the mine 
but a mexican court blocked the transaction citing a law 
forbidding foreign ownership of natural resources according to the 
market rumors 
the ruling was said to have forced the german company to cover 
its market position in london by buying forward contracts which 
caused a massive runup in london said james steel a metals 
analysts with refco inc in new york 
the market was further supported by reports of declining 
warehouse stocks of copper and by production problems in zambia 
analysts said 
bette raptopoulos an analyst with prudentialbache securities 
inc also cited a report that peruvian miners have threatened to 
strike monday at a small stateowned mine and a large peruvian 
copper refinery 
meanwhile a strike at asarco incs ray copper mine in arizona 
stretched into its 11th day wednesday adding another bullish 
factor 
in preciousmetal trading on the commodity exchange gold 
