the counts 
the deliberations followed tuesdays partial verdict in which 
mulheren was convicted of conspiracy and stock manipulation for his 
dealings with admitted insider trader ivan f boesky 
the outstanding charges are allegations that mulheren secretly 
held large blocks of stock to help boesky evade taxes and federal 
securities disclosure laws 
on wednesday the jury reheard testimony about these 
transactions 
the jurors are considering 26 counts of securities fraud mail 
fraud and record keeping violations which each carry up to five 
years in prison and a 250000 fine 
the panel convicted mulheren 41 on four counts of conspiracy 
and securities fraud which carry the same penalty 
codefendant leonard destefano 34 a former trader at 
mulherens defunct firm jamie securities was acquitted tuesday of 
all conspiracy and recordkeeping violations charges brought 
against him 
