<TEXT>
fannie mae the secondary mortgage market 
company said wednesday that second quarter earnings rose 50 
percent in part because of a drop in home foreclosures 
earnings were 2896 million or 110 per share up from 193 
million or 75 cents per share in the same period a year earlier 
fannie mae formally the federal national mortgage association 
is a congressionally chartered but shareholderowned company that 
buys mortgages from lenders 
it packages many mortaes into securities for resale to investors 
and is responsible for financing about one of every eight home 
purchases 
fannie mae chairman david o maxwell attributed the performance 
to an increase in the margin between the interest it earns and the 
interest it pays a rise in fee income and a drop in mortgage 
foreclosures 
the company acquired 2315 properties through foreclosure in the 
second quarter down from 2455 in the first quarter it was the 
lowest number since 1984 
</TEXT>
