<TEXT>
public service co of new mexico said 
wednesday it is reviewing a tentative proposal from wheeler capital 
corp to buy the new mexico utility for 12 per share 
jb bud mulcock jr pnms senior vice president of 
corporate affairs and secretary described the proposal as a 
preliminary expression of interest concerning a possible business 
combination 
wheeler peak has not submitted a formal proposal but has 
suggested a possible transaction in which pnm shareholders would 
receive 12 per share in cash and a portion of the common equity of 
the surviving company mulcock said in a prepared statement 
released by pnm 
pnm had 418 million shares of common stock outstanding as of 
dec 31 which would make the deal worth about 500 million in cash 
if all shares were bought at the current price 
pnm stock closed at 1175 wednesday up from tuesdays close of 
975 on the new york stock exchange 
mulcock said the company was conducting a preliminary review of 
the wheeler peak expression of interest as part of pnms 
previously announced review of strategic options for maximizing 
shareholder value 
southwestern public service co said in a statement it had held 
preliminary discussions with wheeler peak and was interested in 
acquiring some of pnms electric utility assets it said no 
agrement had been reached 
southwestern public based in amarillo texas serves customers 
in parts of new mexico texas oklahoma and kansas 
pnm had operating revenues in 1989 of 9153 million spokesman 
gayland bryant said he said the company has about 290000 electric 
customers in 25 communities around the state its gas company of 
new mexico serves almost all of new mexico 
pnm has been experiencing financial problems in the past three 
years its stock has fallen to nearly onefourth of its former 
value dividends have been suspended and the companys bond rating 
has been downgraded 
pnm announced this spring that it had hired the investment 
banking firm of morgan stanley to investigate ways in which it 
could improve its return to shareholders including the option of 
selling the entire company 
